Due to its small press nature, publication of Strangehaven has been erratic, with only 18 issues published to date (1995-2005).

All 18 issues have been collected in three Abiogenesis trade paperbacks:

His only way out is to prove he is mentally stable, his therapist/doctor has studied him for years. This Doctor has a strange obsession with him and wants to be with him or to be just like him. The doctor eventually goes into a creepy stalker mode after Deadpool escapes the institution and stalks him all over England.

deck: Memorial is a fantasy series from creators Chris Roberson and Rich Ellis. It features a young woman named Em who has no memory and has inherited a magic shop.
description: New York Times best-selling author and Eisner-nominated creator of iZombie, Chris Roberson, delivers a magical new ongoing series. With art by the fantastical Rich Ellis, and covers by the legendary Michael WM Kaluta. MEMORIAL is the story of Em, a young woman who arrives at a hospital in Portland, Oregon with no memory of her past. A year later, she has managed to rebuild her life, finding a job and friends, when her existence is thrown into turmoil after she inherits a magical shop, the kind that appears in an alley one instant and disappears the next. Em finds herself drawn into a supernatural conflict between immortal beings representing the fundamental aspects of the universe itself. All of existence is at stake, and the only things standing in the way of total oblivion are Em, the magical shop, and a talking cat.
name: Memorial
